@Jordan S I like your wondering about what will happen when companies give out change. Will businesses no longer accept pennies and nickels as payment? How will they adjust their payments and how much they charge for products for consumers who pay cash? 

Taxes are a big part of why products cost a cents amount. Will state legislature have to address this issue if we discontinue the production of coins? 

Keep noticing and wondering!

@Kate Thank you for your thoughtful answers to these questions. I like that you noted a spike for the coins around 2010; I wonder what was going on in the world during that time that contributed to that spike. Do you think that the dime becoming the lowest level of currency would make more things rounded to the nearest 10 cent? Would it incentivize consumers to use coins more or less than they do now? 

How realistic to you think the halting of coin production actually is here in 2025? 

Keep noticing and wondering!
